&gt; maybe one could feed the SpeakJet allophones into EVPmaker. The attached
&gt; WAV file contains the 72 allophones of the SpeakJet chip. (I used
&gt; Audition to cut them out of the sample clip which has been posted here
&gt; recently, and store them in a cue list.) To use this file as an EVPmaker
&gt; source, the &quot;Use Cue List&quot; option must be checked. I have done a few short
&gt; sessions, and got this strange message:
&gt; 
&gt;                 &quot;I little Sir help you eclipse.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; (Doesn&#39;t make any sense to me... lol)
&gt; 
&gt; Of course, this cannot replace a hardware version of SpeakJet, since
&gt; EVPmaker isn&#39;t able to produce the proper transitions between the
&gt; allophones. But maybe it&#39;s worth a try...
&gt; 
&gt; Stefan
